title: Acoustic Elegance: Ultimate Collection - Tingstad & Rumbel
description:
Quote:
By Kurt Harding VINE VOICE
Until recently, I was living blissfully unaware of the music of Eric Tingstad and Nancy Rumbel. So when a Seattle-area friend recommended that I hear them based on her knowledge of some of my other musical interests, I decided to buy a CD and give them a listen. When I looked them up, I was surprised by how much they had recorded without my having previously noticed them, so I settled on Acoustic Elegance: Ultimate Collection because of the large number of tunes offered for my music dollar.

Though the duo's music is hard to classify and perhaps most easily niched as "new age", I find that the best way to describe their sound is as a tranquil sea of sound. So tranquil in fact that although they sound very good, there is little that rises up from that sea of tranquility to really grab the listener. On disc one only Blue Martini, La Fogata, and Lo Que Tu Quisieras came close to doing that. On disc two, those that came closest are Medicine Tree, Oaks, and Aria.

The CD set comes with a folding insert containing album information and some background on the collaboration that made this possible. Acoustic Elegance perhaps is best enjoyed while kicking back relaxing on a weekend morning with a steaming cup of java at hand. This is one I will listen to on occasion, but the mood will have to be right and the time to just vegetate abundant.
